  "text": "This shot recipe tastes just like a gingerbread cookie. It’s the perfect blend of butterscotch schnapps, fireball and heavy cream. Mix all that with some gingerbread syrup for a sweet, spiced shot recipe. Related: Green Tea Shot, Cherry Bomb Shot, Gummy Bear Shot, Pink Starburst Shot. Ingredients Fireball – Cinnamon Whiskey. Buttershots – Butterscotch Schnapps. Heavy Cream – Or Half and Half. Gingerbread Syrup – Make homemade gingerbread syrup or pick up a bottle. Optional Garnish: I garnished the shot glasses with a bit of buttercream icing and crumbled gingerbread cookies. You can also use festive sprinkles as your rim garnish. Equipment Needed: I used my go-to set of tall shot glasses for this recipe. You will also need a cocktail shaker of some kind. If you don’t own a cocktail shaker, you can use a sealed jar or even a water bottle as a shaker. How to Make Gather your ingredients. For this recipe, you’ll need Fireball whiskey, butterscotch schnapps, heavy cream and gingerbread syrup. Combine all ingredients in a cocktail shaker filled with ice and shake for 15 seconds until icy cold. Pour your shot into a shot glass and serve immediately. Next up, I will go over the garnish instructions. If you’re planning to garnish your shot glass with a gingerbread crumb rim, go ahead and crumble one cookie. My favorite way to do this is to throw it into a plastic bag and use a rolling pin to crush it. To rim your shot glass, use some buttercream icing to rim the top and then dip it into the gingerbread crumbles. Tips for Making More garnish ideas – I think these would be so cute with a garnish of colorful sprinkles. You could save your leftover sprinkles from a cookie making session to use here. If you make a batch of gingerbread syrup, be sure to also try our gingerbread latte. I think it would also be delicious in tea or a gingerbread steamer for kids (milk and a little gingerbread syrup, steamed). If you want to make these shots ahead, you can save a pre-made mixture in a bottle in your fridge, but don’t add ice until you are ready to shake and serve them. Frequently Asked QuestionsWhat’s in a Gingerbread Shot? This recipe is made with butterscotch schnapps, Fireball whiskey, heavy cream and gingerbread syrup. What flavor is Gingerbread? Gingerbread is flavored with spices such as ground ginger, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg. More Festive Recipes Christmas Cocktails Homemade Chex Mix Scooby Snack Shot Homemade Eggnog Get our FREE recipe guide with our most popular recipes of all time!Get the Guide Ingredients ▢ ¾ ounce Fireball whiskey▢ ¾ ounce butterscotch schnapps ▢ ½ ounce heavy cream▢ ½ ounce gingerbread syrup ▢ 1 cocktail shaker▢ 1 shot glass Instructions Gather your ingredients. For this recipe, you'll need Fireball whiskey, butterscotch schnapps, heavy cream and gingerbread syrup.Combine all ingredients in a cocktail shaker filled with ice and shake for 15 seconds until icy cold.Pour your shot into a shot glass and serve immediately. More garnish ideas – I think these would be so cute with a garnish of colorful sprinkles. You could save your leftover sprinkles from a cookie making session to use here. If you make a batch of gingerbread syrup, be sure to also try our gingerbread latte. I think it would also be delicious in tea or a gingerbread steamer for kids (milk and a little gingerbread syrup, steamed). If you want to make these shots ahead, you can save a pre-made mixture in a bottle in your fridge, but don’t add ice until you are ready to shake and serve them. Nutrition FactsGingerbread ShotAmount per Serving% Daily Value** Percent Daily Values are based on a 2000 calorie diet.Notice: Nutrition is auto-calculated, using Spoonacular, for your convenience. Where relevant, we recommend using your own nutrition calculations.",
