-Shot.--768x614.jpg 768w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--100x80.jpg 100w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--75x60.jpg 75w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--750x600.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--730x584.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--700x560.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--550x440.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.--156x125.jpg 156w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re planning to garnish your shot glass with a gingerbread crumb rim, go ahead and crumble one cookie. My favorite way to do this is to throw it into a plastic bag and use a rolling pin to crush it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"960\" data-pin-url=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/gingerbread-shot/?tp_image_id=136125\" data-pin-title=\"Gingerbread Shot Recipe\" src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1.jpg 1200w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-300x240.jpg 300w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-768x614.jpg 768w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-100x80.jpg 100w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-75x60.jpg 75w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-750x600.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-730x584.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-700x560.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-550x440.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-156x125.jpg 156w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 1200px) 730px, (min-width: 1080px) 650px, (min-width: 1024px) 630px, calc(100vw - 40px)\" data-old-src=\"data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=\u0026#39;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\u0026#39;%20viewBox=\u0026#39;0%200%201200%20960\u0026#39;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" data-lazy-srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1.jpg 1200w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-300x240.jpg 300w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-1024x819.jpg 1024w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-768x614.jpg 768w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-100x80.jpg 100w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-75x60.jpg 75w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-750x600.jpg 750w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-730x584.jpg 730w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-700x560.jpg 700w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-550x440.jpg 550w, https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1-156x125.jpg 156w\" data-lazy-src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-1.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eTo rim your shot glass, use some buttercream icing to rim the top and then dip it into the gingerbread crumbles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"h-tips-for-making\"\u003eTips for Making \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMore garnish ideas – I think these would be so cute with a garnish of colorful sprinkles. You could save your leftover sprinkles from a cookie making session to use here.\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eIf you make a batch of \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/gingerbread-syrup/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003egingerbread syrup\u003c/a\u003e, be sure to also try our \u003ca href=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/gingerbread-latte/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003egingerbread latte\u003c/a\u003e. I think it would also be delicious in tea or a gingerbread steamer for kids (milk and a little gingerbread syrup, steamed).\u003c/li\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cli\u003eIf you want to make these shots ahead, you can save a pre-made mixture in a bottle in your fridge, but don’t add ice until you are ready to shake and serve them.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch2\u003eFrequently Asked Questions\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cdetails id=\"faq-question-1735326970157\"\u003e\u003csummary\u003e\u003ch3\u003eWhat’s in a Gingerbread Shot? \u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/summary\u003e \u003cp\u003eThis recipe is made with butterscotch schnapps, Fireball whiskey, heavy cream and gingerbread syrup. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/details\u003e \u003cdetails id=\"faq-question-1735330584750\"\u003e\u003csummary\u003e\u003ch3\u003eWhat flavor is Gingerbread? \u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/summary\u003e \u003cp\u003eGingerbread is flavored with spices such as ground ginger, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg. \u003c/p\u003e \u003c/details\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"1200\" height=\"960\" data-pin-url=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/gingerbread-shot/?tp_image_id=136127\" data-pin-title=\"Gingerbread Shot Recipe\" src=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/Gingerbread-Shot.-1-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://abeautifulmess.com/wp-